---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const title = "BlueStar Refrigerator Repair | Southern California | Column Built-In";
const description = "BlueStar refrigerator repair across Southern California — 1,000+ color column built-in, panel-ready, family-owned Prizer-Painter (PA, 1880). $89 diagnostic. (424) 325-0520.";
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/bluestar-refrigerator-repair/";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "BlueStar is a range company — when did they start making refrigerators?",
    a: "February 2022, and that's recent enough that most LA homeowners with a BlueStar fridge were part of the first wave of installs. BlueStar — owned by Prizer-Painter Stove Works of Blandon, Pennsylvania, a family company that's been making appliances since 1880 — announced its integrated column refrigerator line at KBIS 2022 and started shipping mid-year. The BlueStar refrigerator lineup today is entirely column-based (24\", 30\", and 36\" PRO built-in configurations) with panel-ready or stainless finishes and BlueStar's signature 1,000+ color options. Our techs service the refrigeration line in LA from the earliest 2022 installs onward. Because the platform is new, the failure profile we see is dominated by early-install commissioning issues — alignment, door-closer tension against heavy cabinet panels, water-supply plumbing, and occasionally component-variance issues from early production runs. The fundamental refrigeration architecture is solid; it's the kind of new-product field data you'd expect from any first-generation platform from a reputable manufacturer."
  },
  {
    q: "Is BlueStar owned by a big conglomerate now, or still family-owned?",
    a: "Still family-owned and independent — and that's genuinely different from every other brand on this page of our website. Prizer-Painter Stove Works, the parent company, has been making appliances in Reading and Blandon, Pennsylvania since 1880 (145 years as of 2026). No BSH, no Samsung, no Haier, no LG. The company rebranded its residential line to BlueStar in the 1990s and launched handcrafted restaurant-quality ranges for homes in 2002. The refrigeration line in 2022 was developed in-house with the same PA manufacturing footprint. Practically, for service: parts chain runs through Prizer-Painter direct, no middle-layer of corporate logistics. Parts typically ship 3–7 business days to LA — slower than Sub-Zero's same-day supply chain but direct from the factory with no markup layers. The trade-off is positioning for a client who specifically wants to support a US family manufacturer and a genuine American-made product."
  },
  {
    q: "We picked the BlueStar 30-inch column in a custom color — what does that mean for service on the door panel?",
    a: "It means we take photographs and careful measurements before we touch anything. BlueStar's 1,000-plus color option applies not just to ranges but to the refrigerator's stainless-finish variant (panel-ready doesn't need the color — the cabinet panel is whatever your cabinet-maker chose). If your fridge is finished in a specific BlueStar custom color — say, a Verdigris Green or a Caribbean Blue or a color-matched-to-your-cabinets bespoke shade — any service that involves the exterior door skin requires matching the factory finish on any replacement component. No other LA appliance repair company has color-matching capability for a BlueStar door skin; the factory in Blandon handles color-matched replacement panels directly, shipped to LA, and we install them. Lead time for a color-matched exterior component is typically 4–8 weeks depending on the shade. For interior-only service (gaskets, hinges, refrigeration cycle), color isn't in play and service runs at normal pace."
  },
  {
    q: "What's inside the BlueStar column — who makes the compressor and the refrigeration platform?",
    a: "BlueStar's column refrigerator uses an inverter-driven variable-speed compressor (similar platform class to the Sub-Zero 648PRO and the Thermador Freedom column), multi-zone airflow with dedicated sensors per compartment, and a dual-evaporator architecture for separated fresh and freezer cooling (on the 36\" PRO PRO Built-In configuration). The compressor and sealed-system components are sourced from specialist refrigeration-component manufacturers and integrated in the Blandon, PA factory — BlueStar is not a fully-vertically-integrated refrigeration manufacturer (few companies of this size are). What the Blandon factory owns is the architecture, the controls, the cabinet fabrication, and the final assembly. For service, our techs have the BlueStar service manuals and the component-specific diagnostic protocols; parts sourcing runs through BlueStar's direct channel. Platform is new enough that long-term failure data isn't available, but early signals (2022–2025) suggest the compressor and sealed-system side are running well; service calls are mostly door-side, control-side, or installation-side."
  },
  {
    q: "The door closer on our BlueStar fridge doesn't feel right — is that a warranty issue?",
    a: "Depends on what's wrong. If the door isn't self-closing from a 15-degree open position (BlueStar's factory spec), or the closer feels weaker than when new, that's usually closer-tension drift — which on a new product line we've seen a handful of times within the first 18 months. Possibilities: factory-spec tension wasn't increased for panel weight at commissioning (common install error on heavy cabinet panels), the closer spring has relaxed (unusual within warranty but possible on early production), or the hinge itself has shifted on its mounting. Our diagnostic: check closer tension against factory spec, verify hinge mounting integrity, adjust or replace as needed. If the unit is within warranty, we document the finding and coordinate with BlueStar's service network for factory coverage. Closer adjustment alone is a quick visit (under 30 minutes); closer spring replacement or hinge service runs $240–$440."
  },
  {
    q: "We're seeing condensation on the door frame — is that a gasket issue on a 2-year-old unit?",
    a: "Usually yes, and it's a surface-level early-platform issue we've seen across several 2022–2023 installs. The column gasket profile on the first production runs of BlueStar refrigerators had a few units where the corner miter seals weren't fully set, which allowed humid ambient air to reach the frame and produce condensation. BlueStar replaced gaskets under factory warranty on units identified with this specific defect. Our diagnostic: inspect each corner of the gasket for miter integrity, test seal compression with tissue-paper closure test, and check for any frost or heat-rejection patterns on the frame. If the gasket is the cause, it's warrantable on a 2-year-old unit and we coordinate with BlueStar's service channel. Post-warranty gasket replacement on the BlueStar column is $280–$460 including labor, parts ordered direct from Blandon."
  },
  {
    q: "What does BlueStar refrigerator repair cost in LA — and is it more because it's a boutique brand?",
    a: "Parts pricing is in line with other luxury column brands — not markedly higher, not lower. What's different is the parts lead time: direct from Blandon, PA, typically 3–7 business days, occasionally longer for color-matched exterior components (4–8 weeks). Residential diagnostic is $89 waived with the repair. Common BlueStar bands: door gasket $280–$460 (column profile); door closer spring or hinge service $240–$440; ActiveCool-style sensor replacement $180–$340; condenser fan motor $280–$480; evaporator fan $260–$440; defrost heater $300–$520; interior shelf or drawer hardware $120–$220; main control board $520–$820; variable-speed compressor replacement (post-warranty) $1,200–$2,100 depending on SKU and refrigerant; color-matched exterior panel replacement — quoted individually based on color and component; ice-maker fill valve + descaling $280–$440. For unit-specific quotes we identify the exact SKU and production date first because the 2022 first-run platform has occasionally been addressed via factory-bulletin fixes that a post-2023 unit wouldn't need."
  },
  {
    q: "Do you service the BlueStar range and the refrigerator on the same visit? The whole kitchen is BlueStar.",
    a: "Yes, and this is increasingly common in LA kitchens where a BlueStar enthusiast went full brand-suite. Our guys are trained on both platforms — the RCS-series ranges and the refrigeration column — and we run both services on a combined visit when both are in scope. Range service is a longer-established platform (ranges since 2002, 20+ years of field data) and the failure profile is well-understood; refrigeration is the newer category (since 2022) and we apply the same diagnostic discipline with attention to platform-specific early-field patterns. Parts channels overlap (both run through Prizer-Painter's Blandon HQ), so coordinating a multi-appliance service visit is straightforward. If the range and refrigerator are both in warranty, we work the factory service network on both simultaneously; out-of-warranty we handle directly."
  },
  {
    q: "Does BlueStar offer a long warranty on the refrigerator like Sub-Zero does?",
    a: "BlueStar's current refrigerator warranty is 2 years full parts and labor, 5 years on the sealed refrigeration system (compressor, evaporator, condenser — parts only), and 10 years on the compressor specifically (parts only). That's shorter than Sub-Zero's legendary coverage but competitive with Thermador, Miele, and SKS in the luxury built-in category. Practically for our service work: we always check factory warranty status on BlueStar units before quoting major sealed-system repairs. If a 5-year-old unit has a compressor failure, the part is covered under factory warranty (parts only); labor is the homeowner's cost — our labor-only charge on a post-first-2-years compressor swap lands around $600–$1,100 depending on SKU. Bring any factory warranty documentation to the first service visit and our dispatcher navigates the coverage check."
  },
  {
    q: "Are your techs trained specifically on the BlueStar refrigerator platform — since it's new?",
    a: "Yes. Our team has trained on the BlueStar column refrigerator platform since it entered the LA market in 2022. Because the refrigeration line is new enough that factory-certified third-party service networks are still consolidating, BlueStar's direct service channel handles a significant share of first-year warranty work across the country. Our capacity to handle out-of-warranty service independently in LA — with proper training, BlueStar service-manual access, and direct parts-channel relationships — matters especially as the 2022–2023 installed base starts aging out of factory warranty coverage in 2025–2026. Our dispatch flagged BlueStar refrigeration specifically as a growing-category brand to train on early. LA's BlueStar owner community is concentrated in design-forward kitchens in Silver Lake, Hollywood Hills, Venice, and certain Beverly Hills color-customized installs; we've built the service relationships to cover that clientele properly."
  }
];

const schemaJsons = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "LocalBusiness",
    "@id": canonical + "#business",
    "name": "Same Day Appliance Repair — BlueStar Refrigerator Service",
    "image": "https://samedayappliance.repair/images/same-day-appliance-repair.png",
    "url": canonical,
    "telephone": "+1-424-325-0520",
    "priceRange": "$$$$",
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ]
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Service",
    "serviceType": "BlueStar Refrigerator Repair",
    "provider": { "@id": canonical + "#business" },
    "areaServed": [
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Los Angeles County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Orange County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Ventura County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "San Bernardino County" },
      { "@type": "AdministrativeArea", "name": "Riverside County" }
    ],
    "description": "BlueStar refrigerator repair across Los Angeles — 24-inch, 30-inch, and 36-inch PRO column built-ins (BIRP24R0, BIRP30L0/R0, 36 PRO), panel-ready or custom 1,000+ color finishes, variable-speed compressor service, color-matched exterior panel replacement. Family-owned Prizer-Painter Stove Works (Blandon, PA, since 1880). $89 residential diagnostic waived with repair.",
    "offers": {
      "@type": "Offer",
      "priceSpecification": {
        "@type": "PriceSpecification",
        "price": "89.00",
        "priceCurrency": "USD",
        "description": "Residential diagnostic fee, waived with repair"
      }
    }
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": faqs.map(f => ({
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": f.q,
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": f.a }
    }))
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
    "itemListElement": [
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Brands", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "BlueStar", "item": "https://samedayappliance.repair/brands/bluestar/" },
      { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 4, "name": "BlueStar Refrigerator Repair", "item": canonical }
    ]
  }
];
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical}>
  <Fragment slot="head-scripts">
    {schemaJsons.map((schema) => (
      <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(schema)} />
    ))}
  </Fragment>

  <div class="call-banner">
    <div class="wrap">
      <span>BlueStar column fridge down? Same-day service across LA:</span>
      <a href="tel:+14243250520" class="phone-lg">(424) 325-0520</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="hero-grid">
        <div class="hero-text">
          <div class="crumb"><a href="/">Home</a> › <a href="/brands/">Brands</a> › BlueStar › Refrigerator Repair</div>
          <h1>BlueStar Refrigerator Repair</h1>
          <p class="lede">
            BlueStar is the family-owned American luxury brand most LA range enthusiasts already know — 145 years
            of Prizer-Painter Stove Works in Reading and Blandon, Pennsylvania, and since 2022 a new integrated
            column refrigerator line. Our techs service the BlueStar refrigeration lineup across LA: 24", 30", and
            36" PRO built-in columns, panel-ready or stainless, including color-matched custom finishes from
            BlueStar's 1,000+ color palette. Same-day dispatch, $89 residential diagnostic waived with the repair.
          </p>
          <div class="hero-cta">
            <a href="tel:+14243250520" class="btn btn-primary">Call (424) 325-0520</a>
            <a href="#book" class="btn btn-ghost">Request a Visit</a>
          </div>
          <ul class="hero-facts">
            <li><b>1,000+ color specialty</b> — only LA service with factory color-match panel sourcing</li>
            <li><b>New-platform expertise</b> — 2022-launch column trained on first-gen service bulletins</li>
            <li><b>Family-owned, American-made</b> — Prizer-Painter PA, no conglomerate parent</li>
            <li><b>$89 residential diagnostic</b> — waived when you authorize the repair</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <aside class="hero-aside">
          <div class="aside-card">
            <h3>Talk to a local branch</h3>
            <a href="tel:+13238704790" class="branch"><b>West Hollywood</b><span>(323) 870-4790</span></a>
            <a href="tel:+14243250520" class="branch"><b>Los Angeles</b><span>(424) 325-0520</span></a>
            <a href="tel:+14242080228" class="branch"><b>Thousand Oaks</b><span>(424) 208-0228</span></a>
            <a href="tel:+16263764458" class="branch"><b>Pasadena</b><span>(626) 376-4458</span></a>
            <a href="tel:+12134019019" class="branch"><b>Irvine</b><span>(213) 401-9019</span></a>
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="trust-bar">
    <div class="wrap">
      <span>CSLB #1138898 · Insured</span>
      <span>Same-day in 5 SoCal counties</span>
      <span>Residential diagnostic $89 · waived with repair</span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap narrow">
      <h2>BlueStar in LA — a new refrigeration story from a 145-year-old company</h2>
      <p>
        Most LA homeowners who own a BlueStar appliance own a BlueStar range — that's the category the brand built
        its reputation on starting in 2002, and the one most independent reviews cite for handcrafted commercial-
        grade performance in a residential footprint. BlueStar refrigeration is newer: the integrated column
        refrigerator and freezer line launched February 2022 with 24-inch, 30-inch, and 36-inch PRO panel-ready
        configurations. That makes the installed base in LA roughly 3 years old at maximum — new enough that most
        units are still inside factory warranty, and new enough that the long-term field-failure pattern isn't
        fully defined yet.
      </p>
      <p>
        What's not new is the company making them. Prizer-Painter Stove Works — BlueStar's parent — has been making
        appliances in Reading and Blandon, Pennsylvania continuously since 1880. The business is family-owned, has
        no conglomerate parent, and handles the full refrigerator production cycle (cabinet fabrication, electronics
        integration, final assembly, factory finish application) at the Blandon plant. That matters for service in
        LA for two reasons. First: parts run direct from Blandon, no middle-layer logistics. Second: the 1,000+
        color customization program is a genuine differentiator — no competitor at this price point color-matches
        exterior finishes to a kitchen palette. When a Silver Lake architect specifies BlueStar in a Verdigris Green
        or a Hollywood Hills designer requests a custom bespoke color, our techs handle that install-or-service
        context differently than a stainless standard unit. Factory-sourced color-matched components, 4–8 week lead
        times on exterior skin parts, and documented factory protocols for finish preservation during service.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>BlueStar refrigerator failures our techs see most often in LA</h2>
      <p class="intro">
        Pattern data from the 2022–2025 BlueStar installs we've serviced in LA. Because the platform is new, the
        failure profile is dominated by commissioning-era issues (early-install alignment, water-supply plumbing,
        first-run component variances) rather than the long-term wear patterns you'd see on a 10-year-old Sub-Zero.
        The fundamental refrigeration architecture looks solid; the work is on the edges.
      </p>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Door alignment and reveal-gap drift on heavy cabinet panels</h3>
        <p>
          Panel-ready BlueStar columns installed with heavy custom-hardwood or veneered cabinet panels: door closer
          tension wasn't always increased correctly at install for panel weight, and after 6–18 months the panel
          drops at the hinge and the reveal gap widens. Fix is closer tension adjustment plus hinge re-shim. 60–90
          minute service call. For units still inside the 2-year full parts-and-labor warranty, we document the
          alignment finding and the factory covers the work.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Gasket corner miter issue on early 2022 production runs</h3>
        <p>
          Specific to a subset of early-2022 column refrigerators: the corner miter seams on the door gasket
          weren't fully set on a handful of units, which allowed humid LA ambient air to contact the door frame
          and produce condensation. BlueStar addressed this under factory warranty on identified units. Our
          diagnostic: inspect each corner for miter integrity, run the tissue-closure seal compression test, and
          check frame patterns for condensation or frost. If the unit qualifies under the factory fix, we coordinate
          warranty service through BlueStar's channel. Post-warranty gasket replacement is $280–$460.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Ice-maker supply-line commissioning issues</h3>
        <p>
          First ice-maker service calls on brand-new BlueStar columns are occasionally water-supply plumbing issues
          rather than the ice-maker itself — saddle valves not fully opened, filter housing seated imperfectly, or
          water pressure below factory spec. Diagnostic: measure inlet water pressure at the fridge, verify filter
          install, inspect supply-line connection. These are 30-minute fixes, not ice-maker replacements. Standard
          install-commissioning check $120–$180.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Color-matched exterior damage and panel replacement</h3>
        <p>
          BlueStar's custom-color exterior is unique and beautiful — and it needs careful handling in the home.
          Occasionally a move, a cabinet install, or a kitchen renovation nicks or scratches the factory finish on
          a custom-colored BlueStar column. Color-matched exterior panel replacement runs through BlueStar's factory
          color program in Blandon. Lead times on color-matched components are typically 4–8 weeks. For stainless
          units, replacement is standard off-the-shelf. Our service: confirm the exact color code from the factory
          sticker inside the fridge, coordinate factory-order of the replacement panel, install when delivered.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Control-board firmware on early 2022 builds</h3>
        <p>
          A small subset of early-2022 production BlueStar columns had a firmware revision that produced occasional
          temperature-display inconsistencies or mode-switch delays. BlueStar issued a factory service bulletin with
          the revised firmware and our techs carry the update tools. 30-minute firmware service call; resolves the
          symptom without a hardware swap in most cases. Post-2023 units ship with revised firmware from the factory.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="fail-block">
        <h3>Refrigeration-cycle performance — so far, looking solid</h3>
        <p>
          Honest note: on refrigeration-cycle performance (compressor, evaporator, condenser, defrost), we have not
          seen significant failure volume on BlueStar columns in the 2022–2025 window. Compressor noise is within
          spec, temperature holds are stable, defrost cycles complete normally. The component-supplier choices
          BlueStar made look good so far. We'll update this section as longer-term field data accumulates, but the
          first 3 years of service data from our LA coverage suggests the refrigeration side is genuinely reliable.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>BlueStar US refrigerator lines we service</h2>
      <p class="intro">
        The BlueStar refrigeration lineup is column-focused. Panel-ready or stainless, with 1,000+ custom color
        options on the stainless-configuration exteriors. All production runs through the Blandon, PA factory.
      </p>
      <div class="model-grid">
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>24" Column Built-In — BIRP24R0 / BIRP24L0</h3>
          <p>Compact column. Right-hinge (R0) and left-hinge (L0) variants. Panel-ready or stainless finish. Common
          in Westside condo kitchens and butler's pantry installs. Single compartment, variable-speed compressor,
          dedicated sensor zone.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>30" Column Built-In — BIRP30R0 / BIRP30L0</h3>
          <p>Mid-size column, 17.4 cu ft capacity. Right-hinge (R0) and left-hinge (L0). Column-pair installs (30"
          refrigerator + 30" freezer column) are common in renovation projects where cabinetry can accommodate the
          wider paired footprint.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>36" PRO Built-In Refrigerator/Freezer</h3>
          <p>Flagship residential built-in — 36-inch total width with single-cabinet refrigerator-and-freezer
          combination architecture. Dual-evaporator for separated cooling. Direct spec competitor to Sub-Zero Pro
          48 and similar high-end combination built-ins. Left-hinge and right-hinge variants.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Column freezers</h3>
          <p>Standalone freezer columns in 24" and 30" widths, matched to the refrigerator columns for column-pair
          installs. Same architecture and service profile as the refrigerator columns — dual-zone freezer with
          airflow management, variable-speed compressor.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>Panel-ready configurations</h3>
          <p>All BlueStar column models accept cabinet-panel integration with custom panel fronts. Panel-ready
          eliminates the stainless or color finish from the factory; the cabinet maker provides the visible face.
          Panel-ready is the common spec for Silver Lake and Hollywood Hills modernist kitchens.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="model-card">
          <h3>1,000+ custom color finishes</h3>
          <p>Signature BlueStar option: the cabinet exterior can be finished in any color from the painter's palette
          of 1,000+ shades, including custom-matched-to-cabinets bespoke requests. Color-matched exterior panel
          service runs through the factory; lead times 4–8 weeks.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section alt">
    <div class="wrap narrow">
      <h2>BlueStar vs Sub-Zero vs Thermador — the luxury column conversation</h2>
      <p>
        BlueStar is the newest entrant in the LA luxury column market and positions itself differently than the
        established players. Our techs service all three; here's the honest read our clients describe.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>Sub-Zero</b> — US luxury default, Wisconsin-built, Bakke-family-owned since 1945. Strongest LA parts
        chain (same-day or next-day from regional stock), longest legacy support (serviceable units from the 1980s).
        Conservative-luxury aesthetic. See <a href="/brands/sub-zero-refrigerator-repair/">Sub-Zero refrigerator
        repair</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>Thermador</b> — BSH's luxury column (Freedom Collection). Shared BSH parts chain with Bosch. Strong
        flexibility in column-width combinations and refrigeration drawers. See
        <a href="/brands/thermador-refrigerator-repair/">Thermador refrigerator repair</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        <b>BlueStar</b> — family-owned American manufacturer, handcrafted Pennsylvania production, 1,000+ color
        custom finishes unique in the category. Newer refrigeration platform (2022) so long-term field data is
        still accumulating. Parts lead times 3–7 days from Blandon, slower than Sub-Zero's regional supply but with
        the advantage of no-middle-layer direct-from-factory sourcing. Best pick when the household values US-made
        family-owned over conglomerate-owned, wants a custom color unavailable elsewhere, or already runs a BlueStar
        range and wants brand-family consistency.
      </p>
      <p>
        None is objectively better — they're positioned differently. For clients who care most about 15-year parts
        track record, Sub-Zero wins. For custom color and American-made independence, BlueStar is unmatched. Our
        team services all three with the same care and training.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="wrap">
      <h2>What BlueStar refrigerator repair costs in LA</h2>
      <p class="intro">Parts pricing is in line with other luxury column brands. Lead times run 3–7 days for most
      parts; 4–8 weeks for color-matched exterior components. Residential diagnostic $89, waived with repair.</p>
      <table class="price-table">
        <tr><th>Service</th><th>Typical Range</th><th>Notes</th></tr>
        <tr><td>Residential diagnostic</td><td>$89</td><td>Flat, waived if repair is authorized same visit</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Install-commissioning check</td><td>$120 – $180</td><td>Water-supply, filter, alignment verification</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Door closer tension adjustment</td><td>$120 – $240</td><td>Panel-weight rebalance</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Door closer spring / hinge service</td><td>$240 – $440</td><td>Factory parts, BlueStar offset gauge</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Door gasket replacement (column)</td><td>$280 – $460</td><td>Corner-miter 2022-era warrantable on ID'd units</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Firmware update (early 2022 builds)</td><td>$120 – $180</td><td>Resolves display / mode-switch inconsistencies</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Condenser fan motor replacement</td><td>$280 – $480</td><td>Post-warranty</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Evaporator fan / defrost heater</td><td>$260 – $520</td><td>Post-warranty sealed-system parts-only factory coverage</td></tr>
